  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he took a child,.... Which was in the house, and which he called unto him, and set by him, as the other evangelists observe: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and set him in the midst of them; his disciples, that all might see and learn from this instance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and when he had taken him in his arms; and embraced him, to show his great regard to humility, and humble persons: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he said unto them; the following words. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "he said unto them; the following words. ",
            "children": []
