  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 36.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And he took a little child",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "παιδίον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "and set him in the midst of them",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". St. Mark adds, what is not recorded by the other synoptists, that he took him in his arms. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And taking him in his arms",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐναγκαλισάμενος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "folding him in his arms",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "embracing him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It is probable that the house where he was was the house of Simon Peter; and it is possible that this little child might have been Simon's. A tradition not earlier than the ninth century says that this child was Ignatius. Mark 9:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
